  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "WebRTC uses UDP, which means a network connection is never open or closed. It uses timeouts to determine connection state; on a slow CI runner, these timeouts could be reached. Increasing this timeout should reduce flakes, but is unlikely to remove this flake entirely.",
